      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROMEO LIGHTNING (5) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when fifth (32.70) in an A3 at this track. Generally a safe beginner but buried in the ruck from trap five last time. Has a good record here at this journey. The form out of his last race has been franked. Worth another chance. STRICTLY ALEXIS (2) resumed with a plain effort to finish fourth, beaten 9 lengths, in an A7 at this track over 480m (30.21). Suited this easier grade and fitter. Can turn form around. WRAYSBURY QUEEN (3) is heading the right way. In the minors two back with a third then scored by 10 lengths in an A9 last time at this track over 480m (30.14). Rises a grade but can measure up with repeat of latest. BALLYMAC FEARNE (1) surprised many when in the placings last start - deserves some thought.",
